================================================================
This is a grab bag of various Perl scripts, mostly numerical,
and all rather old at this point.

See also http://github.com/johnkerl/scripts
See also http://github.com/johnkerl/scripts-misc

John Kerl
kerl.john.r@gmail.com
2012-07-28
================================================================

Descriptions:

Numerical calculus:
* series estimation [numseries],
* another series estimation [numseries2],
* 1-D numerical differentiation [numderiv1],
* 1-D numerical integration [numint1],
* 2-D numerical integration [numint2],
* path integral one way [numint3],
* same path integral another way [numint4].

Floating-point matrix arithmetic:
* Matrix multiply [pmatmul],
* matrix add [pmatadd],
* matrix inverse [pmatinv],
* determinant [pdet],
* row reduction [prred],
* row echelon form [prech],
* row rank [prank],
* kernel basis [pkerbas],
* Gram-Schmidt orthonormalization [pgramsch],
* Jacobi eigensolver for real symmetric matrices [prseigsys],
* elementwise vector sum [pvecadd],
* elementwise vector difference [pvecsub],
* elementwise vector product [pvecmul],
* vector times scalar [pvecsmul],
* dot product [pdot],
* vector-to-scalar sum [psve],
* vector-to-scalar sum of squares [psvesq],
* matrix library file PMATLIB.pm [PMATLIB.pm].

Generators of special-purpose matrices:
* Hilbert matrix (famously near-singular) [pmkhilbmx],
* identity [pmkI],
* DDA A [pmkddaA],
* DDA Q [pmkddaQ].

Fast Fourier transform and associated tools:
* radix-2 FFT [pfft],
* complex rectangular-to-polar [prect2polar],
* complex polar-to-rectangular [ppolar2rect],
* power sum (for discrete Parseval) [ppowersum].

Data generators for testing FFT implementations:
* pcisgen [pcisgen],
* pspikegen [pspikegen],
* phatgen [phatgen],
* prampgen [prampgen],
* prandgen [prandgen].

Misc. numerical routines:
* Lagrange interpolation [lagrinterp],
* partial sums [sumupx],
* binomial coefficients and Pascal's triangle [binc],
* extended GCD using Blankinship's algorithm [pgcd].
